	<TextInfo>
		<Text Type="Business Summary" lastModified="2015-07-17T04:06:44">Castings P.L.C. is a United Kingdom-based iron casting and machining company. The Company is organized into three operating companies, which are considered to be the operating segments: Castings P.L.C. and William Lee Limited are aggregated into Foundry operations and CNC Speedwell Limited is the Machining operation. Castings P.L.C. (Brownhills) supplies spheroidal graphite (SG) iron castings to a range of manufacturing industries from its mechanized foundries. William Lee Limited supplies spheroidal graphite iron castings from its invested foundries in Dronfield, Derbyshire. CNC Speedwell Limited is an invested machining operation focused on the prismatic machining of iron and aluminum castings in Brownhills and Fradley. It produces ductile iron castings, SG iron castings, austempered ductile iron castings, silicon molybdenum castings and nickel-resist castings.</Text>
		<Text Type="Financial Summary" lastModified="2015-11-17T00:17:37">BRIEF: For the six months ended 30 September 2015, Castings PLC revenues increased 2% to L65M. Net income increased 15% to L7.6M. Revenues reflect Machining segment increase of 24% to L9.9M. Net income benefited from Machining segment income increase of 38% to L2.6M, Foundry Operations segment income increase of 8% to L6.9M. Dividend per share remained flat at L0.03. Basic Earnings per Share excluding Extraordinary Items increased from L0.15 to L0.17.</Text>
	</TextInfo>
